  "uuid": "d2fcee116523e4db24d68ac7b9479b0b",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinate all M&E trades (Mechanical, Electrical, Fire, Plumbing, ELV, BMS).</li><li>Manage M&E coordination drawings / BIM models and resolve clashes.</li><li>Coordinate M&E works with architectural, structural and civil trades.</li><li>Review and coordinate shop drawings, method statements and material submissions.</li><li>Attend and minute M&E coordination meetings.</li><li>Identify potential site issues early and propose coordination solutions.</li><li>Monitor site progress and ensure works follow approved drawings.</li><li>Liaise with consultants, subcontractors and suppliers on technical matters.</li><li>Support statutory inspections and authority requirements (BCA, SCDF, PUB, SP Group).</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or Building Services recognized by the PE Board.</li><li>Minimum 3 years M&E experience in large building or infrastructure projects.</li><li>Proven experience in large-scale projects (arena, stadium, convention centre, airport, hospital\npreferred).</li><li>Good knowledge of ACMV / HVAC systems, Electrical & ELV systems, Fire protection systems,\nPlumbing & drainage and BMS integration.</li><li>Able to read and interpret M&E drawings and specifications.</li></ul>",
